libvr
------------------------------------------
LibVR is a free-software interface to Virtual Reality headsets such as the
Oculus Rift. It is meant to be a simple, portable C library with few
dependencies.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  cygwin-devel-1.7.35-1
  libhidapi-devel-0.8.0-rc1-1
  libhidapi0-0.8.0-rc1-1
  libvr-devel-0.0.1+hg20141110-1bl1
  libvr0-0.0.1+hg20141110-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://hg.sitedethib.com/libvr

Canonical download:
  http://hg.sitedethib.com/libvr

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libvr-0.0.1+hg20141110-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libvr-0.0.1+hg20141110-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libvr-0.0.1+hg20141110-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libvr-0.0.1+hg20141110-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libvr0-0.0.1+hg20141110-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libvr-devel-0.0.1+hg20141110-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libvr)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libvr.README
  /usr/share/doc/libvr/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libvr/README

(libvr0)
  /usr/bin/cygvr-0.dll

(libvr-devel)
  /usr/include/LibVR/display_info.h
  /usr/include/LibVR/hmd.h
  /usr/include/LibVR/stereo.h
  /usr/lib/libvr.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libvr.pc

